1
00:00:36,641 --> 00:00:38,059
Je-sun.

2
00:00:40,686 --> 00:00:41,729
Wait a minute.

3
00:00:42,104 --> 00:00:44,732
- Je-sun.
- I'll pretend I didn't hear you.

4
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:47,193
Just go. Please.

5
00:01:16,597 --> 00:01:19,266
You must get the package before he does.

6
00:01:28,275 --> 00:01:29,819
Je-sun!

7
00:01:30,945 --> 00:01:32,196
Je-sun!

8
00:01:39,453 --> 00:01:41,080
EPISODE 9

9
00:01:42,415 --> 00:01:44,041
Are you okay? You're not hurt?

10
00:01:45,376 --> 00:01:48,295
What... what are you doing here?

11
00:01:50,715 --> 00:01:52,842
How... how did you get here?

12
00:01:54,552 --> 00:01:55,553
Director.

13
00:01:56,178 --> 00:01:58,597
Director, please open your eyes!

14
00:02:00,808 --> 00:02:02,601
Oh, Director!

15
00:02:05,479 --> 00:02:06,814
Director!

16
00:02:10,151 --> 00:02:11,277
Director!

17
00:02:11,944 --> 00:02:13,487
- She's not badly hurt.
- All right.

18
00:02:13,571 --> 00:02:15,156
- Let's get her out of here.
- Okay.

19
00:02:21,704 --> 00:02:26,584
Look how smoothly this car is going.
Darn, this is fun to drive.

20
00:02:33,841 --> 00:02:35,718
What the... Gang Beom-ryong?

21
00:02:44,852 --> 00:02:46,687
His face looks kind of familiar.

22
00:02:57,072 --> 00:02:58,657
Hey, what's going on?

23
00:02:59,909 --> 00:03:03,204
Hey, Kkot-nim, are you okay? Hey.

24
00:03:03,913 --> 00:03:07,166
Hey, what happened?

25
00:03:07,249 --> 00:03:09,502
- We were attacked, Boss.
- Attacked? Who attacked you?

26
00:03:10,711 --> 00:03:12,546
- Gang Beom-ryong?
- No.

27
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:14,298
- It was some other guy.
- Another guy?

28
00:03:14,381 --> 00:03:16,509
He showed up out of nowhere
and grabbed Kim Seon-jung's wife

29
00:03:16,592 --> 00:03:17,760
and the woman we saw at the house.

30
00:03:17,843 --> 00:03:19,136
- Yes, that woman.
- He took them and disappeared.

31
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:20,221
He took them and...

32
00:03:20,304 --> 00:03:22,640
Darn it! Seriously. Gosh, my leg.

33
00:03:22,723 --> 00:03:23,933
Hey, you idiots! What are you doing?

34
00:03:24,016 --> 00:03:26,435
- Get out here, now!
- Boss, what about Kkot-nim?

35
00:03:26,519 --> 00:03:27,812
Just leave that idiot.
Get out here, quick.

36
00:03:28,312 --> 00:03:29,605
Darn it.

37
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,306
They say it's a mild concussion.

38
00:04:05,641 --> 00:04:08,978
I think she'll have to be admitted
to the hospital for observation.

39
00:04:12,815 --> 00:04:14,066
How do you two know each other?

40
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,777
She's the wife
of one of my high school teachers.

41
00:04:16,861 --> 00:04:17,862
A teacher?

42
00:04:20,364 --> 00:04:22,658
What kind of teacher
has gangsters looking for him?

43
00:04:25,035 --> 00:04:29,373
What are you trying to imply?
It's not what you think.

44
00:04:29,456 --> 00:04:32,418
Stay away from him for a while.
Don't get mixed up in this.

45
00:04:34,211 --> 00:04:37,339
- What do you know to be saying this?
- Because I'm worried.

46
00:04:38,257 --> 00:04:40,718
My wife almost got dragged away by thugs.

47
00:04:40,801 --> 00:04:42,011
As her husband,
I'm not allowed to say that?

48
00:04:42,094 --> 00:04:44,179
No, you're not.

49
00:04:46,056 --> 00:04:48,934
About how you showed up there earlier

50
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,729
or what that whole fight was about...

51
00:04:52,187 --> 00:04:53,898
Have you ever once given me
a proper explanation?

52
00:04:53,981 --> 00:04:54,982
No, that's...

53
00:04:55,566 --> 00:04:58,277
- What's that got to do with this?
- How could it not?

54
00:05:03,657 --> 00:05:04,909
You...

55
00:05:06,327 --> 00:05:08,162
You've been acting so suspiciously lately

56
00:05:08,996 --> 00:05:11,874
and you haven't even given me
a proper explanation for what's going on.

57
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:15,377
What wife in the world
would listen to a husband like that?

58
00:05:15,461 --> 00:05:16,670
What reason do I have to trust you?

59
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:28,933
Honey.

60
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:31,602
Are you, by any chance...

61
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:35,856
keeping a secret
that I'm not supposed to know?

62
00:05:39,485 --> 00:05:40,569
Is that it?

63
00:05:51,872 --> 00:05:52,873
O-ran!

64
00:05:53,999 --> 00:05:55,876
Oh, Mr. Kim!

65
00:05:57,252 --> 00:05:58,712
How is my wife?

66
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:02,383
She's all right. This way, please.

67
00:06:37,793 --> 00:06:39,128
Get lost, you idiots.

68
00:06:39,461 --> 00:06:41,714
Get out. What are you looking at?
Get back to work. Now.

69
00:06:44,508 --> 00:06:47,386
So you're saying
you failed to tie up the loose ends?

70
00:06:48,178 --> 00:06:50,973
I'm sorry. It's just that
some guy showed up out of nowhere--

71
00:06:51,056 --> 00:06:52,975
And this guy who showed up out of nowhere

72
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:56,228
was with Gang Beom-ryong,
Hwasan Sect's number two?

73
00:06:56,311 --> 00:06:57,312
So why?

74
00:06:58,313 --> 00:07:00,107
You had no idea who this guy was?

75
00:07:00,524 --> 00:07:04,987
Well, that's the thing.
He definitely looked familiar, but...

76
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:08,032
- I just can't place him--
- If you say you can't remember

77
00:07:09,074 --> 00:07:10,576
then what am I supposed to do?

78
00:07:10,659 --> 00:07:12,786
It wasn't that so-called
Martial Arts Master, was it?

79
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:14,246
No, it was someone else.

80
00:07:20,085 --> 00:07:22,129
Mr. Nam, the owner
of the van that appeared

81
00:07:22,212 --> 00:07:23,881
in front of Kim Seon-jung's house
and at the port.

82
00:07:24,048 --> 00:07:25,049
Have you identified him?

83
00:07:25,132 --> 00:07:26,675
We ran a check, but it was a ghost car.

84
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:28,010
A ghost car?

85
00:07:32,306 --> 00:07:33,599
My goodness.

86
00:07:34,349 --> 00:07:36,977
Now things are starting to become clear.

87
00:07:37,102 --> 00:07:40,064
- What?
- The masked guys Yoo was chasing.

88
00:07:41,273 --> 00:07:43,942
This mysterious man and Gang Beom-ryong.

89
00:07:44,026 --> 00:07:45,360
It fits perfectly, doesn't it?

90
00:07:46,445 --> 00:07:47,696
Oh, right.

91
00:07:48,363 --> 00:07:50,741
Now that you mention it... I see.

92
00:07:50,824 --> 00:07:52,826
Gang Beom-ryong,
number two of the Hwasan Sect

93
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:54,787
the martial arts master,
and the mystery man.

94
00:07:55,204 --> 00:07:57,581
For skilled fighters like them
to just pop up

95
00:07:57,664 --> 00:08:00,417
and interfere with our business
at every turn.

96
00:08:01,210 --> 00:08:02,711
This can't be a coincidence.

97
00:08:03,087 --> 00:08:06,924
I have a feeling
they're specifically targeting one of us

98
00:08:07,007 --> 00:08:08,717
and this is all part of a plan,
don't you think?

99
00:08:08,801 --> 00:08:11,303
Darn it, but why the hell would they?

100
00:08:13,097 --> 00:08:16,266
If we just find one more puzzle piece,
we'll have our answer.

101
00:08:18,268 --> 00:08:21,980
- Chairman Do, should I handle this?
- Handle it?

102
00:08:23,649 --> 00:08:24,650
How?

103
00:08:24,733 --> 00:08:26,735
If we grab Gang Beom-ryong
and beat it out of him

104
00:08:26,819 --> 00:08:27,986
we'll get our answer, won't we?

105
00:08:28,821 --> 00:08:30,322
- Beat it out of him?
- Yes.

106
00:08:30,614 --> 00:08:32,199
- Gang Beom-ryong.
- Yes.

107
00:08:34,409 --> 00:08:36,495
Well, I don't know about that.

108
00:08:37,496 --> 00:08:40,916
Mr. Geum, back when you were
just shining shoes for the Hwasan Sect

109
00:08:40,999 --> 00:08:44,086
wasn't Gang Beom-ryong already
their second-in-command?

110
00:08:45,712 --> 00:08:47,464
Even if you do catch a guy like that
and try to beat him

111
00:08:47,548 --> 00:08:49,883
do you really think he'd talk to you

112
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:53,971
who's so far beneath him?
I mean, a man has his pride.

113
00:08:54,388 --> 00:08:56,557
- Am I wrong?
- Well...

114
00:08:57,391 --> 00:09:00,144
Chairman Do, actually,
I wasn't that low on the totem pole.

115
00:09:00,227 --> 00:09:02,354
- In the Hwasan Sect, I was--
- For now

116
00:09:02,938 --> 00:09:05,149
Mr. Geum, just focus
on managing Heaven Capital.

117
00:09:05,399 --> 00:09:07,025
- But, Chairman--
- Do you understand?

118
00:09:07,651 --> 00:09:08,652
Chairman...

119
00:09:10,195 --> 00:09:11,405
I asked if you got it.

120
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:13,991
Yes, I understand.

121
00:09:16,076 --> 00:09:17,369
Let's go.

122
00:09:27,212 --> 00:09:28,505
Darn it.

123
00:09:33,635 --> 00:09:35,721
As if he could beat it out of him.

124
00:09:36,221 --> 00:09:38,724
Mr. Nam, do you have anyone competent?

125
00:09:38,932 --> 00:09:42,311
I need someone who can handle
this job cleanly, with no fuss.

126
00:09:42,603 --> 00:09:45,522
- There are some very skilled hitmen.
- Hitmen?

127
00:09:46,732 --> 00:09:49,610
Okay. Hitmen. I like it.

128
00:09:50,277 --> 00:09:52,321
Set them up right away.

129
00:09:52,988 --> 00:09:55,199
And Mr. Nam,
you should get warmed up, too.

130
00:09:55,991 --> 00:09:58,994
Man, you must have been feeling
cooped up, stuck behind a desk.

131
00:09:59,328 --> 00:10:01,663
It's about time
you got out in the field again.

132
00:10:02,414 --> 00:10:03,999
Yes, sir.

133
00:10:27,314 --> 00:10:29,107
What's with all this drama?

134
00:10:33,445 --> 00:10:34,988
Are you sure about this?

135
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:37,032
I'm going to come clean.

136
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,035
I have to.

137
00:10:41,495 --> 00:10:42,496
O-ran.

138
00:10:43,455 --> 00:10:44,706
Her family.

139
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:47,960
And the people of Yeongseon Island.

140
00:10:48,627 --> 00:10:50,128
Before they're in even more danger.

141
00:10:50,921 --> 00:10:52,089
From now on

142
00:10:52,839 --> 00:10:54,216
I have to be more aggressive.

143
00:10:55,717 --> 00:10:56,969
All right.

144
00:10:58,095 --> 00:11:00,806
Then I guess I'll take this chance
to properly introduce myself to your wife.

145
00:11:02,683 --> 00:11:05,102
So after you tell her everything

146
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,854
what happens next?

147
00:11:09,856 --> 00:11:12,609
First, I'm going to meet
with Candidate Kim Seon-jung

148
00:11:13,777 --> 00:11:15,362
and hear what he has to say.

149
00:11:31,878 --> 00:11:33,338
MY LITTLE BROTHER

150
00:11:33,672 --> 00:11:35,090
Jeez, you scared me.

151
00:11:37,426 --> 00:11:39,553
Hey, why aren't you answering my calls?

152
00:11:39,678 --> 00:11:40,679
I was busy.

153
00:11:40,971 --> 00:11:44,224
For a guy who never answers his phone
to be looking for me

154
00:11:44,725 --> 00:11:45,934
means you got your butt kicked again.

155
00:11:46,018 --> 00:11:47,227
No, it's not like that.

156
00:11:47,311 --> 00:11:48,979
What do you mean it's not like that?

157
00:11:49,062 --> 00:11:50,772
I can tell just from your voice.

158
00:11:51,773 --> 00:11:52,774
So who was it this time?

159
00:11:53,984 --> 00:11:58,447
- This fake Yankee jerk.
- Yankee? A foreigner?

160
00:11:58,530 --> 00:12:02,617
I'll explain the details when we meet,
so can you come to where I am now?

161
00:12:02,701 --> 00:12:03,702
All right.

162
00:12:03,785 --> 00:12:05,787
- I'll go once I wrap things up here.
- Hey!

163
00:12:06,621 --> 00:12:10,000
The kimchi stew is ready.
Why aren't you coming? Jeez.

164
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:11,626
I was on the phone with In-gu.

165
00:12:15,922 --> 00:12:17,883
For crying out loud. Geez.

166
00:12:18,884 --> 00:12:22,012
In-gu? He got beat up again?

167
00:12:22,262 --> 00:12:25,682
- That's just In-gu for you.
- What an idiot.

168
00:12:25,766 --> 00:12:28,268
So where is he now?

169
00:12:44,951 --> 00:12:48,955
Yes, Mi-kyung, it's me.
I'm at the hospital right now.

170
00:12:49,748 --> 00:12:53,126
No, not me. Je-sun got a little hurt.

171
00:12:54,336 --> 00:12:56,088
Yes. I'm sorry to ask

172
00:12:56,171 --> 00:12:58,757
but could you tell Nam-il
to come to the hospital?

173
00:13:28,703 --> 00:13:29,913
Hey.

174
00:13:30,914 --> 00:13:32,165
Who's there?

175
00:13:44,886 --> 00:13:46,054
I'm sorry.

176
00:13:52,477 --> 00:13:54,563
- Who are you?
- I couldn't ring the doorbell

177
00:13:54,938 --> 00:13:56,523
because there were too many prying eyes.

178
00:13:58,191 --> 00:13:59,234
O-ran!

179
00:13:59,317 --> 00:14:00,318
Oh, Mr. Kim!

180
00:14:20,630 --> 00:14:23,258
So the reason you dropped out of the race

181
00:14:24,217 --> 00:14:26,511
was because of Han Gyeong-wook's scheme.

182
00:14:26,595 --> 00:14:28,430
I was too naive.

183
00:14:29,055 --> 00:14:34,352
I never imagined
that he'd attack me like this.

184
00:14:34,436 --> 00:14:37,147
You don't need to blame yourself.
About Han Gyeong-wook...

185
00:14:37,814 --> 00:14:39,232
Ever since his days
at the National Intelligence Service

186
00:14:39,316 --> 00:14:42,903
he has specialized in plots,
threats, and things like that.

187
00:14:42,986 --> 00:14:44,946
Since I couldn't stop
Candidate Han Gyeong-wook

188
00:14:45,655 --> 00:14:49,367
I'm worried there will be more victims

189
00:14:50,744 --> 00:14:53,330
like with the orphanage
and the Heaven Capital debtors.

190
00:14:57,751 --> 00:15:00,212
- We have to stop him somehow.
- Alone?

191
00:15:01,087 --> 00:15:04,716
Do you think that's possible?
Those scumbags...

192
00:15:05,383 --> 00:15:07,302
They are a force to be reckoned with.

193
00:15:07,594 --> 00:15:09,513
I know exactly what they are like.

194
00:15:10,972 --> 00:15:12,682
I'll deal with them.

195
00:15:13,058 --> 00:15:15,727
You just focus on what you have to do

196
00:15:16,186 --> 00:15:20,148
- for the people of Yeongseon Island.
- Okay.

197
00:15:20,899 --> 00:15:22,108
I understand.

198
00:15:23,735 --> 00:15:25,946
I can't take back my withdrawal.

199
00:15:27,197 --> 00:15:29,699
But if there's anything I can do to help

200
00:15:30,075 --> 00:15:33,411
- just let me know.
- Thank you.

201
00:15:35,497 --> 00:15:36,831
Oh, and...

202
00:15:39,251 --> 00:15:40,418
About the place

203
00:15:41,378 --> 00:15:43,129
where my wife is helping the victims.

204
00:15:44,005 --> 00:15:45,840
Is it possible to know where that is?

205
00:15:47,050 --> 00:15:51,471
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

206
00:16:00,647 --> 00:16:03,108
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

207
00:16:04,234 --> 00:16:06,736
WE CAN'T BACK DOWN FROM REDEVELOPMENT
THAT KILLS THE COMMON PEOPLE!

208
00:16:13,994 --> 00:16:16,329
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

209
00:16:16,413 --> 00:16:18,582
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

210
00:16:21,418 --> 00:16:22,919
- Where's Ji-woo's mom?
- She said

211
00:16:23,003 --> 00:16:25,213
she had a dance club meeting
and left suddenly.

212
00:16:25,297 --> 00:16:26,298
Again?

213
00:16:26,756 --> 00:16:29,050
Has she gone crazy for dancing?
What's with her lately?

214
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:32,053
HANMAEUM SOCIAL DANCE

215
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:48,486
Bulgae's nephew?

216
00:16:58,913 --> 00:17:01,166
YEONGSON MEDICAL CENTER

217
00:17:01,249 --> 00:17:02,834
Uncle!

218
00:17:05,545 --> 00:17:06,546
What happened?

219
00:17:06,838 --> 00:17:10,300
How can someone who went on a date
become a hit-and-run victim?

220
00:17:11,301 --> 00:17:13,970
- Is he badly hurt?
- There are no external injuries

221
00:17:14,429 --> 00:17:16,806
so don't worry too much.
He'll wake up soon.

222
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:20,226
Darn it.

223
00:17:22,812 --> 00:17:25,649
I've explained the schedule
for his checkups.

224
00:17:25,732 --> 00:17:27,817
So, who will be staying with him?

225
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:29,986
- I'll stay.
- All right.

226
00:17:30,445 --> 00:17:32,697
- You?
- Je-sun got hurt because of me

227
00:17:33,198 --> 00:17:34,407
so I think it's only right that I stay.

228
00:17:34,491 --> 00:17:36,785
No, even so, his nephew should stay.

229
00:17:36,868 --> 00:17:39,079
Please give me a chance to repay him.

230
00:17:39,162 --> 00:17:42,582
When I fell into the sea,
Je-sun was the one who took care of me.

231
00:17:45,001 --> 00:17:47,504
Can I ask you something?

232
00:17:48,713 --> 00:17:50,924
What do you think of my uncle?

233
00:17:52,509 --> 00:17:54,094
- What do you mean?
- What?

234
00:17:54,177 --> 00:17:56,763
- Excuse me?
- No, I mean...

235
00:17:57,972 --> 00:17:59,808
Do you find my uncle...

236
00:18:05,271 --> 00:18:06,272
Never mind.

237
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,817
Don't worry about it. Okay.

238
00:18:08,942 --> 00:18:11,569
I should... I should get going.

239
00:18:11,653 --> 00:18:13,196
- Okay.
- Bye.

240
00:18:15,990 --> 00:18:17,117
Hey.

241
00:18:19,411 --> 00:18:21,329
- Have a good time.
- What?

242
00:18:21,788 --> 00:18:22,914
With my uncle.

243
00:18:43,393 --> 00:18:44,644
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae?

244
00:18:45,228 --> 00:18:46,271
Who might you be?

245
00:18:48,314 --> 00:18:49,858
So we finally meet.

246
00:18:55,363 --> 00:18:58,575
So Yoo In-gu has already been cut loose?

247
00:18:58,658 --> 00:19:01,244
Yes. What's more, a man named Chairman Do

248
00:19:01,327 --> 00:19:03,079
took over everything Yoo In-gu was doing.

249
00:19:03,163 --> 00:19:06,291
So Han Gyeong-wook
won't be affected at all.

250
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,753
Instead, why not focus
on what you mentioned earlier?

251
00:19:09,836 --> 00:19:12,005
The package containing
Han Gyeong-wook's weakness

252
00:19:12,422 --> 00:19:15,175
- and try looking for that?
- The package?

253
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,260
I mean, you said you have
the radio receiver.

254
00:19:17,552 --> 00:19:19,137
So is there really no way to find it?

255
00:19:20,472 --> 00:19:24,100
The receiver is supposed to go off
when I get within 10m of the package

256
00:19:24,184 --> 00:19:27,729
but I've searched all over
Yeongseon Island for the past ten years

257
00:19:27,812 --> 00:19:29,397
and the receiver has never gone off.

258
00:19:30,273 --> 00:19:33,359
I even went to Bulgae's house,
but there was no signal there either.

259
00:19:34,569 --> 00:19:36,237
It seems Bulgae

260
00:19:36,321 --> 00:19:40,241
likely hid it in a secret place
only he knows.

261
00:19:42,494 --> 00:19:44,746
Je-sun probably doesn't know
about the package.

262
00:19:46,498 --> 00:19:47,624
Right now

263
00:19:47,707 --> 00:19:51,002
you seem to think
Bong Je-sun is faking his amnesia.

264
00:19:51,211 --> 00:19:52,337
But no.

265
00:19:52,837 --> 00:19:56,257
The Je-sun I saw wasn't faking it.

266
00:20:03,181 --> 00:20:07,227
Since we have no leads on that package,
we need to find another way, and fast.

267
00:20:07,435 --> 00:20:10,688
I heard Han Gyeong-wook is deeply involved
in the recent redevelopment project

268
00:20:10,772 --> 00:20:12,273
on Yeongseon Island.

269
00:20:12,357 --> 00:20:14,651
- Yes.
- Seeing how he's pushing to become mayor

270
00:20:14,734 --> 00:20:16,361
and even mobilizing Heaven Capital

271
00:20:16,444 --> 00:20:18,613
this can't be just an ordinary project.

272
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:22,492
Please look into what's going on
behind the scenes of that project.

273
00:20:23,159 --> 00:20:24,702
Here on Yeongseon Island

274
00:20:24,786 --> 00:20:27,205
we'll dig into the activities of that guy

275
00:20:27,288 --> 00:20:28,581
Chairman Do and Han Gyeong-wook.

276
00:20:29,374 --> 00:20:32,001
All right. I'll investigate
as soon as I get back to the office.

277
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:36,214
And you have to get the dance club members
to back off from this.

278
00:20:36,673 --> 00:20:39,968
- They could be in danger.
- Well...

279
00:20:40,426 --> 00:20:43,888
They're Yeongseon Island natives
who are directly tied to this issue

280
00:20:43,972 --> 00:20:47,600
- so it won't be easy to persuade them.
- I'll try to persuade them myself.

281
00:20:47,892 --> 00:20:50,895
- You will?
- It's about my wife, after all.

282
00:20:52,272 --> 00:20:53,606
That's true.

283
00:20:55,942 --> 00:20:58,111
All right. Let's proceed that way, then.

284
00:20:58,361 --> 00:20:59,445
Okay.

285
00:21:36,941 --> 00:21:38,610
What is it, so late?

286
00:21:43,865 --> 00:21:46,534
About your wife...
Did things get resolved?

287
00:21:47,619 --> 00:21:50,914
Before I go and take care of it,
there's something I need to tell you.

288
00:21:53,082 --> 00:21:55,251
Why Officer Park Mi-kyung was there

289
00:21:55,543 --> 00:21:57,420
and what her relationship is with Bulgae.

290
00:21:58,379 --> 00:21:59,672
I've figured it all out.

291
00:22:04,636 --> 00:22:07,597
But Mi-kyung is just a patrol officer.
What can she do?

292
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:09,599
I mean, does she even know
who she's up against?

293
00:22:09,974 --> 00:22:12,560
She doesn't know what it's like
because she hasn't been through it.

294
00:22:18,900 --> 00:22:21,110
Hey. If you were me

295
00:22:22,528 --> 00:22:23,780
what would you do?

296
00:22:24,364 --> 00:22:27,951
- You tell her to quit right now.
- Hey, it's easier said than done.

297
00:22:28,326 --> 00:22:29,911
If I bring up my past

298
00:22:29,994 --> 00:22:31,913
and tell Mi-kyung to quit what she's doing

299
00:22:31,996 --> 00:22:33,790
you think I don't know how she'd react?

300
00:22:34,207 --> 00:22:35,792
Would the words come easily
if you were me?

301
00:22:35,875 --> 00:22:37,710
So you know she's walking into danger

302
00:22:38,127 --> 00:22:39,671
and you're just going to stand by
and watch?

303
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:45,635
Because you're scared
of what she'll think of you

304
00:22:46,094 --> 00:22:49,180
- you'll just sit back and do nothing?
- Who said I would do nothing?

305
00:22:49,597 --> 00:22:51,766
Think about what's really important.

306
00:22:52,684 --> 00:22:56,562
Your pride or her safety.

307
00:23:22,755 --> 00:23:25,174
- Where's Ji-woo?
- At the restaurant.

308
00:23:26,175 --> 00:23:27,844
I left him with my dad for a little while.

309
00:23:28,219 --> 00:23:30,847
I couldn't let Ji-woo see us fight.

310
00:23:43,234 --> 00:23:44,986
I thought you'd be here yesterday

311
00:23:46,362 --> 00:23:47,613
but you're just showing up now?

312
00:23:48,906 --> 00:23:50,533
That's just like you.

313
00:23:51,951 --> 00:23:53,119
I needed to clear my head.

314
00:23:53,202 --> 00:23:55,246
Not because you were busy
thinking up an excuse?

315
00:24:00,668 --> 00:24:03,838
I was so buried in my own work

316
00:24:04,672 --> 00:24:06,924
that I didn't even realize
what you were going through

317
00:24:07,258 --> 00:24:08,885
or what you were getting into.

318
00:24:09,927 --> 00:24:11,721
I wasn't paying attention
like I should have.

319
00:24:14,974 --> 00:24:16,601
The K-Pop dance club.

320
00:24:17,852 --> 00:24:19,937
You don't go there just to dance, do you?

321
00:24:21,272 --> 00:24:23,357
- What?
- I met with Kim Seon-jung.

322
00:24:24,233 --> 00:24:27,445
He asked me to make you quit
what you're doing.

323
00:24:29,238 --> 00:24:30,865
You were looking into me.

324
00:24:32,075 --> 00:24:34,327
Helping the victims of Heaven Capital.

325
00:24:34,911 --> 00:24:37,413
I get what you're trying to do,
but you need to stop.

326
00:24:37,955 --> 00:24:39,457
They aren't just gangsters.

327
00:24:39,540 --> 00:24:42,835
What do you know that gives you the right
to tell me to stop?

328
00:24:42,919 --> 00:24:43,920
I know them very well.

329
00:24:46,214 --> 00:24:48,382
They're the ones who made me this way.

330
00:24:49,425 --> 00:24:50,551
What?

331
00:24:55,973 --> 00:25:00,144
Do you remember what I told you?
About why I came to Yeongseon Island.

332
00:25:02,605 --> 00:25:04,398
You said that
you were at a trading company

333
00:25:04,816 --> 00:25:07,485
and you were framed for embezzlement
and kicked out.

334
00:25:07,902 --> 00:25:10,822
- You came here to clear your head.
- That was a lie.

335
00:25:19,038 --> 00:25:20,873
The place I worked...

336
00:25:29,590 --> 00:25:31,050
It was the National Intelligence Service.

337
00:25:32,093 --> 00:25:35,054
I was a black ops agent for the NIS.

338
00:25:38,141 --> 00:25:39,559
A black ops agent?

339
00:25:40,601 --> 00:25:44,397
You mean like in the movies,
shooting guns and breaking in?

340
00:25:44,772 --> 00:25:47,400
- Is that what you're talking about?
- Yes, something like that.

341
00:25:47,525 --> 00:25:48,776
Well, do you by any chance...

342
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:51,487
Do you have a criminal record?

343
00:25:51,571 --> 00:25:53,197
Is that why you're telling
this ridiculous lie...

344
00:25:53,281 --> 00:25:54,532
I know it's hard to believe.

345
00:25:56,117 --> 00:25:59,120
I was framed during an operation
and had to go on the run.

346
00:25:59,203 --> 00:26:00,788
I came to Yeongseon Island

347
00:26:00,872 --> 00:26:02,832
to find a clue that would clear my name.

348
00:26:03,958 --> 00:26:06,502
Well, I didn't think ten years would go by

349
00:26:06,586 --> 00:26:09,213
but the person who framed me
and forced me on the run

350
00:26:09,297 --> 00:26:13,259
is now using Heaven Capital
to plot something on Yeongseon Island.

351
00:26:13,509 --> 00:26:15,219
He's extremely dangerous.

352
00:26:17,638 --> 00:26:18,931
So, just for a little while

353
00:26:19,557 --> 00:26:20,892
close the restaurant

354
00:26:22,018 --> 00:26:24,270
- and leave Yeongseon Island.
- So then...

355
00:26:25,730 --> 00:26:31,694
From the very beginning,
you've been lying to me for ten years.

356
00:26:35,781 --> 00:26:37,033
I'm sorry.

357
00:26:39,702 --> 00:26:40,995
Once I cleared my name

358
00:26:41,078 --> 00:26:42,580
and was reinstated at the NIS

359
00:26:43,581 --> 00:26:44,749
I planned to tell you in a grand way.

360
00:26:44,832 --> 00:26:46,792
So I could proudly face you
and our Ji-woo.

361
00:26:46,876 --> 00:26:47,960
Clear your name?

362
00:26:49,629 --> 00:26:50,880
Is that why

363
00:26:50,963 --> 00:26:52,965
you were always out
running around like that?

364
00:26:53,382 --> 00:26:54,675
I mean, how...

365
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:59,055
How could you do something like that
without even consulting me?

366
00:26:59,222 --> 00:27:02,725
And who are you to tell me
to leave Yeongseon Island?

367
00:27:03,768 --> 00:27:05,186
I mean, right now

368
00:27:05,269 --> 00:27:07,271
where would I even go?
I have nowhere to go.

369
00:27:11,609 --> 00:27:14,445
Oh, the dance club. Go stay there for now.

370
00:27:14,695 --> 00:27:17,531
There are no security cameras there,
and it seems safe.

371
00:27:17,865 --> 00:27:20,576
Since they know your face,
they'll use security cameras to track

372
00:27:20,701 --> 00:27:23,746
you, your father, and our Ji-woo.

373
00:27:23,829 --> 00:27:25,915
There's no telling what they'll do.

374
00:27:27,083 --> 00:27:28,376
Our Ji-woo?

375
00:27:36,175 --> 00:27:37,885
The fact that up until now

376
00:27:40,221 --> 00:27:42,098
I couldn't be honest with you...

377
00:27:43,599 --> 00:27:44,725
I'm truly sorry.

378
00:27:44,809 --> 00:27:47,937
I know that you're angry
and it's hard to accept the situation.

379
00:27:48,604 --> 00:27:51,023
I'd feel the same way
if I were in your shoes.

380
00:27:51,107 --> 00:27:53,526
But, just this once

381
00:27:53,901 --> 00:27:54,944
for our family

382
00:27:55,319 --> 00:27:58,572
and for our Ji-woo's sake,
please do as I say.

383
00:28:00,366 --> 00:28:03,077
Please trust me
and just for a little while

384
00:28:05,413 --> 00:28:06,664
go somewhere safe.

385
00:28:09,083 --> 00:28:10,710
I'm begging you, O-ran.

386
00:28:17,925 --> 00:28:19,176
Leave.

387
00:28:21,470 --> 00:28:23,472
You're a husband
who lied to me for ten years.

388
00:28:23,931 --> 00:28:26,017
I don't know how
I'm supposed to trust you.

389
00:28:29,687 --> 00:28:31,314
Give me some time to think.

390
00:28:36,152 --> 00:28:37,403
All right.

391
00:28:38,529 --> 00:28:40,156
Let me know when you're ready.

392
00:29:08,684 --> 00:29:09,727
Hey, you.

393
00:29:14,565 --> 00:29:16,359
- Never mind.
- Geez, come on.

394
00:29:17,109 --> 00:29:19,278
You can't even ask him one thing?

395
00:29:20,863 --> 00:29:21,864
Ho-myeong.

396
00:29:22,239 --> 00:29:27,078
Are you really
an NIS agent or whatever it's called?

397
00:29:27,495 --> 00:29:31,457
It's just that we overheard
you and O-ran fighting.

398
00:29:39,799 --> 00:29:42,009
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you all sooner.

399
00:29:42,218 --> 00:29:44,595
So it's true. It is.

400
00:29:49,683 --> 00:29:51,102
- Mi-kyung.
- My goodness.

401
00:29:53,646 --> 00:29:54,939
You startled me.

402
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:57,775
What are you doing here?

403
00:29:58,651 --> 00:29:59,693
Could you spare

404
00:30:00,778 --> 00:30:03,614
a moment to talk with me?

405
00:30:21,799 --> 00:30:23,384
It's so late

406
00:30:24,301 --> 00:30:26,387
that my convenience store
is the only place still open.

407
00:30:26,512 --> 00:30:27,555
It's fine.

408
00:30:28,472 --> 00:30:30,516
We don't need to talk for long anyway.

409
00:30:31,142 --> 00:30:32,893
You don't have much time, do you?

410
00:30:34,186 --> 00:30:36,939
- Excuse me?
- That's what your employee told me.

411
00:30:37,314 --> 00:30:39,150
That you're someone with big plans

412
00:30:39,608 --> 00:30:41,944
so you don't have time
for someone like me.

413
00:30:42,027 --> 00:30:43,654
That's absolutely not true.

414
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:47,283
- I apologize on his behalf.
- It's fine.

415
00:30:48,742 --> 00:30:50,870
It went in one ear and out the other.

416
00:30:53,205 --> 00:30:55,499
So, what did you want to say?

417
00:30:56,542 --> 00:30:57,585
The reason

418
00:30:58,544 --> 00:31:00,463
I couldn't make it to our meeting that day

419
00:31:01,422 --> 00:31:03,299
was because I didn't want to tell you

420
00:31:04,341 --> 00:31:05,885
about my past.

421
00:31:06,802 --> 00:31:07,845
Your past?

422
00:31:08,929 --> 00:31:10,639
Yes, I...

423
00:31:11,348 --> 00:31:13,350
Before I became the owner
of this convenience store

424
00:31:17,438 --> 00:31:19,273
I was in a gang.

425
00:31:22,651 --> 00:31:23,986
A gang?

426
00:31:26,447 --> 00:31:27,448
Wait.

427
00:31:28,741 --> 00:31:31,744
You're not talking about
being a gangster, are you?

428
00:31:32,286 --> 00:31:33,746
That's right. A gangster.

429
00:31:34,163 --> 00:31:36,081
The kind that uses his fists
and beats people up.

430
00:31:37,416 --> 00:31:38,834
That's the kind of gangster I was.

431
00:31:42,546 --> 00:31:44,465
Is that why you came looking for me?
To tell me this?

432
00:31:44,548 --> 00:31:45,549
Mi-kyung.

433
00:31:47,843 --> 00:31:50,804
It's because I found out
what you've been up to recently.

434
00:31:51,555 --> 00:31:53,098
What you're doing right now

435
00:31:53,182 --> 00:31:54,808
and the stuff related to Heaven Capital.

436
00:31:57,019 --> 00:31:58,312
You need to stop.

437
00:32:03,067 --> 00:32:04,568
Those guys at Heaven Capital.

438
00:32:04,652 --> 00:32:07,738
They're not the kind of people
a patrol officer like you can handle.

439
00:32:08,113 --> 00:32:11,075
If they think you're in their way,
they'll get rid of you

440
00:32:11,158 --> 00:32:12,159
without a second thought.

441
00:32:12,243 --> 00:32:15,204
So all this stuff you're doing,
just stop all of it.

442
00:32:16,288 --> 00:32:17,873
If you get caught,
you'll be in big trouble.

443
00:32:21,210 --> 00:32:23,337
What right do you have

444
00:32:23,504 --> 00:32:26,173
to suddenly show up
and tell me what to do?

445
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:28,676
I mean, it's not like
we've even been on a date.

446
00:32:28,759 --> 00:32:31,136
You have no right to tell me what to do.

447
00:32:34,598 --> 00:32:35,849
And...

448
00:32:36,976 --> 00:32:39,478
in case you forgot, I'm a police officer.

449
00:32:41,188 --> 00:32:44,066
The kind that arrests gangsters
and throws them in jail.

450
00:32:45,734 --> 00:32:47,278
And yet you're telling me

451
00:32:47,778 --> 00:32:50,322
to quit because you know better
as an ex-gangster?

452
00:32:53,534 --> 00:32:55,578
- How could you say that?
- I know.

453
00:32:56,078 --> 00:32:58,539
I knew how you'd see me
if I told you this.

454
00:32:58,622 --> 00:33:00,833
But I couldn't stand by
when it's so obvious

455
00:33:00,916 --> 00:33:02,251
you're walking into danger.

456
00:33:03,377 --> 00:33:05,045
- I couldn't pretend not to know.
- Why?

457
00:33:06,547 --> 00:33:08,173
You should have just pretended
you didn't know.

458
00:33:09,091 --> 00:33:10,342
Then we could have just stayed

459
00:33:11,594 --> 00:33:14,179
as the store owner and a customer.

460
00:33:15,097 --> 00:33:17,558
That's all we could have been,
couldn't we?

461
00:33:17,975 --> 00:33:22,646
I don't care how you see me.

462
00:33:23,647 --> 00:33:26,108
In any case, for your own safety

463
00:33:27,151 --> 00:33:29,486
I hope you'll give my words
one more serious thought.

464
00:33:34,825 --> 00:33:36,619
I should get going.

465
00:34:36,303 --> 00:34:39,723
MY DAD

466
00:34:43,602 --> 00:34:45,145
For our family

467
00:34:45,229 --> 00:34:48,399
and for our Ji-woo's sake,
please do as I say.

468
00:34:49,233 --> 00:34:51,694
Please trust me
and just for a little while

469
00:34:52,319 --> 00:34:53,696
go somewhere safe.

470
00:34:54,196 --> 00:34:55,864
I'm begging you, O-ran.

471
00:36:20,699 --> 00:36:22,659
Yeongseon Steel.

472
00:36:39,843 --> 00:36:41,678
My savior.

473
00:36:49,937 --> 00:36:51,188
Family.

474
00:37:05,661 --> 00:37:08,413
Je-sun, in the field...

475
00:37:08,747 --> 00:37:11,291
The doll.

476
00:37:14,336 --> 00:37:15,671
The doll.

477
00:37:53,125 --> 00:37:54,376
Darn it.

478
00:37:59,464 --> 00:38:03,468
The receiver is supposed to go off
when I get within 10m of the package.

479
00:38:20,569 --> 00:38:23,071
You're here? Boss, hold on.

480
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:25,490
What's with your eyes?
Are you sick or something?

481
00:38:25,949 --> 00:38:29,077
- They're really red.
- Let's hurry. We'll be late.

482
00:38:44,176 --> 00:38:46,637
Seriously, what kind
of K-pop dance team is this?

483
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:49,181
They've got Prosecutor Gang,
Bulgae, and the cop.

484
00:38:49,932 --> 00:38:51,767
And on top of that, even Mr. Jeong's wife.

485
00:38:52,851 --> 00:38:55,896
Hey, Ho-myeong. How did your wife take it?

486
00:38:58,398 --> 00:39:00,359
Of course she's very disappointed.

487
00:39:00,817 --> 00:39:05,697
So, as soon as I crush Yoo In-gu,
Chairman Do, and Han Gyeong-wook

488
00:39:06,031 --> 00:39:07,282
and we talk again...

489
00:39:10,661 --> 00:39:12,162
I hope she'll understand then.

490
00:39:12,913 --> 00:39:13,914
Right.

491
00:39:14,498 --> 00:39:16,792
We just have to finish
before it's too late. Then...

492
00:39:17,376 --> 00:39:20,754
That angry look in her eyes
will probably die down a bit.

493
00:39:32,933 --> 00:39:36,561
So, based on your talk
with Prosecutor Gang yesterday

494
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:39,398
what we need to do at this point

495
00:39:39,856 --> 00:39:42,901
is to dig into what this
redevelopment project is all about, right?

496
00:39:42,985 --> 00:39:44,277
There's definitely
something shady about it.

497
00:39:44,611 --> 00:39:47,072
Han Gyeong-wook must have bribed
someone at the Imcheon city hall.

498
00:39:47,322 --> 00:39:50,701
You should head over there
and find out everything about the project.

499
00:39:51,159 --> 00:39:53,704
We'll go meet Prosecutor Gang
and wrap things up.

500
00:39:53,787 --> 00:39:55,622
Okay. I'll hurry.

501
00:39:59,376 --> 00:40:01,128
- Let's go.
- Yes, let's go.

502
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,880
- Hey, Gong-bok.
- Yes?

503
00:40:07,217 --> 00:40:09,678
Well... About Mi-kyung.

504
00:40:12,889 --> 00:40:14,933
- Never mind.
- It's nothing, right?

505
00:40:20,105 --> 00:40:21,148
Darn it.

506
00:40:21,231 --> 00:40:23,650
What is it? What?
What about that police officer?

507
00:40:23,734 --> 00:40:26,153
Well... No matter how much
I think about it

508
00:40:26,236 --> 00:40:29,364
spying on the Heaven Capital guys
is just too dangerous.

509
00:40:29,448 --> 00:40:31,825
So, I want you to go and...

510
00:40:33,493 --> 00:40:34,786
You want me to what?

511
00:40:34,870 --> 00:40:37,372
- You want me to watch over her?
- I mean...

512
00:40:38,331 --> 00:40:42,335
It is related to our work, after all.
And that area is your specialty.

513
00:40:42,461 --> 00:40:44,087
Why should I use my specialty for that?

514
00:40:44,171 --> 00:40:46,923
She's a cop. She can take care of herself.

515
00:40:47,049 --> 00:40:50,177
Come on, how can you be so heartless?

516
00:40:50,260 --> 00:40:53,430
I mean, she's a long-time customer.
Think of it as customer service.

517
00:40:53,513 --> 00:40:55,974
Just go and support her
if she needs anything.

518
00:40:56,058 --> 00:40:58,101
We closed down the convenience store.

519
00:40:58,185 --> 00:40:59,936
What damn customer service
are you talking about?

520
00:41:00,812 --> 00:41:03,106
Fine. Just forget it.

521
00:41:12,365 --> 00:41:14,576
- I just have to watch her, right?
- Yes.

522
00:41:15,077 --> 00:41:16,661
You know me, right? I'm allergic to cops.

523
00:41:16,745 --> 00:41:19,539
- This is the last time.
- I know, Gong-bok. Let's go.

524
00:41:21,583 --> 00:41:22,793
Gosh, seriously.

525
00:41:52,948 --> 00:41:54,491
We've located their base.

526
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:43,248
Excuse me.
Have you seen Bong Je-sun from room 1301?

527
00:42:43,331 --> 00:42:44,958
- Bong Je-sun?
- Yes.

528
00:42:45,041 --> 00:42:47,294
He was here when I checked
his blood pressure last night.

529
00:42:47,752 --> 00:42:50,338
- He's not in his room?
- Oh, okay. I understand.

530
00:43:00,056 --> 00:43:02,100
Bong Je-sun is gone.

531
00:43:02,767 --> 00:43:06,688
- When? When did he disappear?
- I don't know.

532
00:43:06,771 --> 00:43:08,523
He was gone when I woke up this morning.

533
00:43:09,107 --> 00:43:10,901
His clothes are gone too

534
00:43:10,984 --> 00:43:12,652
and he hasn't been officially discharged.

535
00:43:12,903 --> 00:43:16,239
Where did he go? Are we going to lose him?

536
00:43:16,823 --> 00:43:20,785
I knew this would happen,
so I put a tracker on him yesterday.

537
00:43:21,703 --> 00:43:23,330
Look at you.

538
00:43:23,413 --> 00:43:25,290
There's that old NIS training.

539
00:43:25,498 --> 00:43:27,667
So, where is that guy now?

540
00:43:31,087 --> 00:43:32,923
What? What's wrong with this thing?

541
00:43:33,298 --> 00:43:35,217
What? It says he's still in the hospital.

542
00:43:35,300 --> 00:43:37,552
But I already searched
the entire hospital.

543
00:43:44,768 --> 00:43:45,936
What?

544
00:43:56,154 --> 00:43:57,697
Look at this guy.

545
00:43:57,781 --> 00:43:59,866
So, what happened?
Did we lose him, or what?

546
00:44:00,283 --> 00:44:01,534
I think he figured it out.

547
00:44:03,036 --> 00:44:04,371
Figured what out?

548
00:44:04,454 --> 00:44:07,374
I told you. Bulgae is not an amnesiac.

549
00:44:07,457 --> 00:44:10,627
He was afraid his act would be blown
after seeing me yesterday

550
00:44:10,710 --> 00:44:12,087
so he must have run away.

551
00:44:16,258 --> 00:44:18,510
What? Prosecutor Gang, what are you doing?

552
00:44:19,719 --> 00:44:21,137
Je-sun.

553
00:44:28,186 --> 00:44:31,189
I heard the chicken soup here
is delicious.

554
00:44:38,571 --> 00:44:41,324
- My gosh.
- Just look at this place. Darn it.

555
00:44:42,742 --> 00:44:44,577
It's cozy.

556
00:44:46,371 --> 00:44:47,789
My goodness.

557
00:44:47,998 --> 00:44:49,457
HWANG HWA-SAN SENTENCED TO LIFE
FOR MURDERING KWON SOON-BOK

558
00:44:49,541 --> 00:44:52,961
- These darn stalkers. Darn it.
- What?

559
00:44:54,921 --> 00:44:58,008
Mr. Geum, you are quite photogenic.

560
00:45:07,183 --> 00:45:08,560
THE DEATH OF NATIONAL SECURITY DIRECTOR
KWON SOON-BOK

561
00:45:23,408 --> 00:45:24,409
REPUBLIC OF KOREA PASSPORT

562
00:45:31,875 --> 00:45:33,335
What?

563
00:45:33,918 --> 00:45:35,295
Chairman.

564
00:45:37,630 --> 00:45:42,802
I think we came to the right place.
Man, I really don't get it.

565
00:45:44,012 --> 00:45:48,391
It doesn't seem to be about money.
So why are they pulling this crap?

566
00:45:51,144 --> 00:45:52,687
Take a look at this photo.

567
00:45:55,190 --> 00:45:59,194
SEPTEMBER 2010, FEBRUARY 2010, MAY 2010

568
00:46:13,833 --> 00:46:18,338
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

569
00:46:21,716 --> 00:46:24,803
If you don't pay next time,
I won't be making any more deliveries.

570
00:46:25,970 --> 00:46:27,430
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

571
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:29,974
- Oh, right!
- Gosh, you scared me.

572
00:46:30,558 --> 00:46:32,018
The Chinese food delivery guy.

573
00:46:33,228 --> 00:46:34,687
Chairman, that guy...

574
00:46:35,021 --> 00:46:37,899
- He was with Gang Beom-ryong
- The day before yesterday?

575
00:46:39,025 --> 00:46:40,777
- The delivery guy?
- Yes.

576
00:46:49,327 --> 00:46:51,246
So this is how it all connects.

577
00:46:53,957 --> 00:46:56,751
You put the camper van back
to how it was, right?

578
00:46:57,001 --> 00:47:00,630
Yes. I even planted a bug, as instructed.

579
00:47:01,756 --> 00:47:03,216
Okay, good job.

580
00:47:03,299 --> 00:47:06,428
We absolutely cannot leave
a single trace that we were there.

581
00:47:06,511 --> 00:47:10,348
And for now, tell the hitmen
to just tail them.

582
00:47:10,432 --> 00:47:12,350
Wouldn't it be better to eliminate them?

583
00:47:12,434 --> 00:47:14,644
No. Absolutely not.

584
00:47:15,812 --> 00:47:18,648
The way I see it, these guys
and Deputy Director Han have a past

585
00:47:18,731 --> 00:47:22,193
and I'm sure there's
some spectacular drama involved.

586
00:47:22,277 --> 00:47:24,404
Didn't you see the news clippings

587
00:47:24,487 --> 00:47:26,698
about the ferry incident
from ten years ago and the Hwasan Sect?

588
00:47:26,948 --> 00:47:29,784
You take one look
and the answer is obvious.

589
00:47:29,993 --> 00:47:33,997
If their target was Han from the start,
that means I'm holding a hand

590
00:47:34,080 --> 00:47:35,999
with far more to gain than lose, right?

591
00:47:36,082 --> 00:47:39,377
I can't just throw away a lucky hand
that fell into my lap.

592
00:47:39,461 --> 00:47:41,254
What are you planning to do?

593
00:47:43,214 --> 00:47:45,592
To be the winner in this game

594
00:47:45,675 --> 00:47:49,554
you need to hold a few jokers
to shake up the board.

595
00:47:50,513 --> 00:47:54,434
For now, maybe I'll poke
at Deputy Director Han first?

596
00:47:56,811 --> 00:47:58,605
Gosh, this will be fun.

597
00:47:59,898 --> 00:48:01,357
I'm curious

598
00:48:02,358 --> 00:48:04,903
how he'll react.

599
00:48:07,739 --> 00:48:12,410
Yes, I confirmed he left the hospital
and hailed a taxi.

600
00:48:12,494 --> 00:48:13,745
YEONGSON MEDICAL CENTER

601
00:48:13,828 --> 00:48:15,205
And...

602
00:48:16,581 --> 00:48:19,125
He returned to the hospital
exactly five hours later.

603
00:48:19,834 --> 00:48:23,046
Got it. Send me the video.

604
00:48:43,316 --> 00:48:44,901
Like I said

605
00:48:44,984 --> 00:48:47,278
I just went out to get something to eat.

606
00:48:47,695 --> 00:48:50,198
At that hour? After pulling out your IV?

607
00:48:50,406 --> 00:48:51,533
Yes.

608
00:48:52,325 --> 00:48:55,370
Prosecutor Gang was having a hard time
because of me

609
00:48:55,453 --> 00:48:56,663
sleeping in a chair at the hospital.

610
00:48:56,746 --> 00:48:58,915
So I wanted to repay her somehow.

611
00:48:58,998 --> 00:49:00,917
Why would you say that's on you, Je-sun?

612
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:02,752
You were injured trying to save me.

613
00:49:03,503 --> 00:49:06,089
Then what about this tracking device
that was on your hoodie?

614
00:49:06,714 --> 00:49:08,383
Why did you deliberately remove it
before you left?

615
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:09,801
Tracking...

616
00:49:10,468 --> 00:49:12,303
I had this on me?

617
00:49:13,346 --> 00:49:14,681
Why?

618
00:49:15,348 --> 00:49:16,641
Playing dumb, are you?

619
00:49:16,724 --> 00:49:19,686
No, I'm not playing dumb.
I really didn't know it was there.

620
00:49:21,646 --> 00:49:24,941
Maybe it fell off
when I put the hoodie on?

621
00:49:30,321 --> 00:49:31,573
To be honest...

622
00:49:32,699 --> 00:49:35,910
About what you two and Prosecutor Gang
told me about my past...

623
00:49:35,994 --> 00:49:40,039
I still can't believe it.
I'm just an ordinary office worker.

624
00:49:42,208 --> 00:49:45,628
The idea that I was
such a strong and ruthless agent...

625
00:49:48,172 --> 00:49:51,926
But since you all say so, it must be true.

626
00:49:52,176 --> 00:49:55,221
Even though I don't remember

627
00:49:55,305 --> 00:49:58,641
if I did something wrong
to you two in the past

628
00:49:58,725 --> 00:50:03,313
I want to apologize now.
Yes, I'm truly sorry.

629
00:50:32,425 --> 00:50:35,928
Oh my, Je-sun.
My goodness, what are you doing?

630
00:50:37,013 --> 00:50:38,222
Ho-myeong, what was that for?

631
00:50:38,306 --> 00:50:40,016
He took the hit on purpose.
Can't you see that?

632
00:50:40,099 --> 00:50:41,601
- Oh my, Je-sun.
- Hey.

633
00:50:41,726 --> 00:50:44,687
- Drop the act, you goddamn spy.
- It hurts so much.

634
00:50:44,771 --> 00:50:46,898
Geez, don't you think that's too much?

635
00:50:46,981 --> 00:50:48,775
He's a patient who hasn't fully recovered.

636
00:50:48,900 --> 00:50:52,028
Yes, even I couldn't have dodged that.
Did you have to throw it that hard?

637
00:50:52,111 --> 00:50:54,280
Look, Prosecutor,
you don't seem to get it.

638
00:50:54,364 --> 00:50:57,241
This guy is Bulgae, the most elite agent
of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces.

639
00:50:57,325 --> 00:50:59,160
In the middle of Washington, D.C.,
he evaded the CIA

640
00:50:59,243 --> 00:51:00,912
and helped
all the North Korean hackers escape.

641
00:51:00,995 --> 00:51:03,164
In Sichuan province,
he beat 20 Triad men to a pulp.

642
00:51:03,247 --> 00:51:05,375
He's Bulgae, a human weapon
trained by North Korea.

643
00:51:05,458 --> 00:51:09,003
- He's not a pushover.
- I think you've got it wrong.

644
00:51:09,087 --> 00:51:11,255
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

645
00:51:11,339 --> 00:51:13,633
Look how frail he is.
How's he supposed to take on the CIA?

646
00:51:13,716 --> 00:51:16,678
Get real. You need to make sense.

647
00:51:19,222 --> 00:51:20,556
Yes.

648
00:51:22,433 --> 00:51:23,601
I...

649
00:51:24,727 --> 00:51:27,647
I must have been a really terrible person.

650
00:51:28,106 --> 00:51:31,818
Seeing how you're still this angry
at me after ten years...

651
00:51:31,901 --> 00:51:33,277
I really...

652
00:51:34,112 --> 00:51:36,489
I really don't remember anything.

653
00:51:36,572 --> 00:51:39,867
But I sincerely apologize. I am so sorry.

654
00:51:40,618 --> 00:51:42,120
What's with the sudden apology?

655
00:51:42,203 --> 00:51:43,663
- Exactly.
- Are you okay?

656
00:51:43,746 --> 00:51:46,416
This is not a situation
where you need to apologize.

657
00:51:46,499 --> 00:51:49,919
I'm telling you, it's an act!
Hey, you're a hell of an actor.

658
00:51:50,002 --> 00:51:52,964
Where did you learn to act?
Do they teach that in North Korea now?

659
00:51:53,047 --> 00:51:55,883
- Hey, wait.
- Okay.

660
00:51:56,634 --> 00:52:00,638
I can't atone for my past mistakes,
but perhaps...

661
00:52:00,722 --> 00:52:03,933
Is there a way I can help you two?

662
00:52:04,767 --> 00:52:07,228
- Help us?
- Yes.

663
00:52:07,478 --> 00:52:10,022
- What the hell are you plotting?
- Hey, what's wrong with you?

664
00:52:10,106 --> 00:52:13,317
I'm not plotting anything.
I'm doing this for me. For myself.

665
00:52:13,401 --> 00:52:15,361
That package
I supposedly disappeared with.

666
00:52:15,445 --> 00:52:18,364
If I just have that package,
you said you could stop

667
00:52:18,448 --> 00:52:20,700
what the Heaven Capital guys
are planning, right?

668
00:52:21,242 --> 00:52:23,578
I have a score to settle
with those guys, too.

669
00:52:25,037 --> 00:52:28,458
I just figured if I stick with you two,
the ones who know my past

670
00:52:28,541 --> 00:52:31,294
maybe I'll start to remember something.

671
00:52:31,919 --> 00:52:33,588
Hey, listen to him. It all makes sense.

672
00:52:33,671 --> 00:52:35,548
If he gets his memory back
and we find the package

673
00:52:35,631 --> 00:52:37,008
isn't that the best
we can hope for right now?

674
00:52:41,179 --> 00:52:44,265
I'll go get you another one
of those drinks you were drinking.

675
00:52:44,348 --> 00:52:47,185
- No, it's fine. Are you okay?
- Yes.

676
00:52:48,978 --> 00:52:51,814
Gosh, it hurts so much.

677
00:52:52,064 --> 00:52:53,316
Oh, dear.

678
00:52:58,613 --> 00:53:01,574
That's definitely not an act. My goodness.

679
00:53:05,995 --> 00:53:07,789
That darn scumbag.

680
00:53:26,724 --> 00:53:30,269
- This woman.
- That's Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

681
00:53:30,770 --> 00:53:34,190
I think Yoo must have botched the job.

682
00:53:41,572 --> 00:53:43,282
Gosh, but still...

683
00:53:43,366 --> 00:53:44,909
A Chinese restaurant owner,
a convenience store owner

684
00:53:44,992 --> 00:53:46,619
and an office worker.

685
00:53:46,702 --> 00:53:49,038
They may look like nobodies on the outside

686
00:53:49,121 --> 00:53:51,249
but there's something
suspiciously professional

687
00:53:51,332 --> 00:53:52,875
about the way they operate.

688
00:53:52,959 --> 00:53:55,294
I mean, starting from
when they hit Capital

689
00:53:55,378 --> 00:53:57,672
and then the whole thing with
ruining President Yoo's drug shipment.

690
00:53:57,755 --> 00:53:59,632
Seriously, what's their motive?

691
00:53:59,715 --> 00:54:03,052
Why do they keep interfering
with our business at every turn?

692
00:54:03,135 --> 00:54:05,471
I just don't get it.

693
00:54:07,014 --> 00:54:08,224
By any chance

694
00:54:08,307 --> 00:54:11,519
I was just wondering
if you might have any hunches, sir.

695
00:54:11,602 --> 00:54:13,688
Chairman Do, you must have
a lot of time on your hands.

696
00:54:14,355 --> 00:54:15,648
Pardon?

697
00:54:17,066 --> 00:54:19,318
Worrying about such useless things.

698
00:54:20,778 --> 00:54:23,823
Oh, no, sir. Of course not.

699
00:54:23,906 --> 00:54:26,576
With preparing
for the Yeongseon Island Project

700
00:54:26,951 --> 00:54:28,703
I'm already stretched thin as it is.

701
00:54:29,787 --> 00:54:31,622
Right, so I'll just stop looking into this

702
00:54:31,706 --> 00:54:34,709
- and I'll wrap it up on my end.
- No, wait a minute.

703
00:54:35,751 --> 00:54:37,169
There's something I need to check.

704
00:54:39,130 --> 00:54:40,381
Understood.

705
00:54:41,799 --> 00:54:43,634
The owner of a Chinese restaurant.

706
00:54:46,304 --> 00:54:48,514
He's really moved up in the world.

707
00:54:54,645 --> 00:54:58,316
I'm heading back to my office.
I've got work to do.

708
00:54:58,941 --> 00:55:01,694
Prosecutor, I know
it's not my place to say

709
00:55:02,987 --> 00:55:05,448
but are you sure you should be
getting involved in this?

710
00:55:05,948 --> 00:55:08,993
Han Gyeong-wook has connections
in the Prosecutors' Office too.

711
00:55:09,577 --> 00:55:11,662
You could face pressure
from unexpected places.

712
00:55:12,371 --> 00:55:15,958
I came all the way to Yeongseon Island
and even had my life threatened.

713
00:55:16,042 --> 00:55:18,210
I even found out exactly
what those jerks are really like.

714
00:55:18,294 --> 00:55:20,588
You think I'm going to back down
over a little pressure?

715
00:55:21,297 --> 00:55:22,715
I'll risk my career to expose everything

716
00:55:22,798 --> 00:55:26,469
Han Gyeong-wook has done
and plans to do in the future.

717
00:55:27,261 --> 00:55:28,846
I will make him pay for his crimes.

718
00:55:30,306 --> 00:55:33,309
- What about Chairman Hwang's case?
- Right. I need to figure out

719
00:55:33,392 --> 00:55:35,686
how to properly reinvestigate
that case as well.

720
00:55:37,188 --> 00:55:39,315
- Thank you, Prosecutor.
- Of course.

721
00:55:41,233 --> 00:55:43,736
Hey. Can I talk to you?

722
00:55:44,487 --> 00:55:45,488
What?

723
00:55:54,288 --> 00:55:56,040
Well...

724
00:55:57,249 --> 00:56:00,002
About the hit-and-run driver
who hit you...

725
00:56:00,086 --> 00:56:02,713
I will catch them no matter what,
so don't you worry.

726
00:56:03,756 --> 00:56:05,424
Oh, okay.

727
00:56:05,508 --> 00:56:07,134
Is that what you wanted to talk about?

728
00:56:07,218 --> 00:56:08,970
Yes, that's part of it.

729
00:56:10,304 --> 00:56:14,934
I realized I never got the chance
to properly thank you.

730
00:56:15,017 --> 00:56:18,187
- Thank me for what?
- You saved my life. Twice.

731
00:56:18,896 --> 00:56:21,691
- I'm truly grateful.
- Oh, it was nothing.

732
00:56:21,774 --> 00:56:24,235
As long as you're okay, Prosecutor,
that's all that matters.

733
00:56:26,404 --> 00:56:27,822
I think you're a really good person.

734
00:56:28,531 --> 00:56:29,532
Me?

735
00:56:32,785 --> 00:56:34,620
The Bong Je-sun I've seen

736
00:56:36,789 --> 00:56:39,709
is someone who truly looks out for others.

737
00:56:40,793 --> 00:56:42,128
A good person.

738
00:56:44,088 --> 00:56:48,009
Even if you happen to go back
to your old self

739
00:56:50,052 --> 00:56:52,680
my gratitude toward you will never change.

740
00:56:56,767 --> 00:57:00,521
- Let me see your phone for a second.
- Oh, my phone?

741
00:57:14,577 --> 00:57:15,995
It's my number.

742
00:57:16,078 --> 00:57:18,414
It's not my work number.
It's my personal one.

743
00:57:18,831 --> 00:57:22,460
I don't give this number to anyone,
but I'm making an exception for you.

744
00:57:22,585 --> 00:57:24,920
But why are you giving this to me...

745
00:57:25,212 --> 00:57:26,881
Because I owe you.

746
00:57:27,965 --> 00:57:32,678
Save that number,
and call me if you ever need my help.

747
00:57:34,013 --> 00:57:37,641
Anytime. For anything. Just once.

748
00:57:37,892 --> 00:57:39,935
I'll help you out, no questions asked.

749
00:57:54,658 --> 00:57:57,995
Are you really going to keep him around?

750
00:57:58,287 --> 00:57:59,830
Why? You have a problem with it?

751
00:57:59,914 --> 00:58:03,000
No. To me, it seemed like
he really didn't remember anything.

752
00:58:03,084 --> 00:58:05,586
So I'm just wondering
if we really need to keep him with us.

753
00:58:05,669 --> 00:58:07,379
He also said he can't control
when his skills come back, right?

754
00:58:07,463 --> 00:58:08,464
Then he's just dead weight.

755
00:58:08,547 --> 00:58:11,884
Don't tell me you actually believe
Bulgae lost his memory.

756
00:58:13,552 --> 00:58:14,845
Don't you?

757
00:58:20,184 --> 00:58:23,813
Look. This is the CCTV footage
from near the hospital Gong-bok sent over.

758
00:58:24,647 --> 00:58:26,565
He said he went out
for chicken soup earlier, right?

759
00:58:26,690 --> 00:58:28,734
But there's a chicken soup place
right in front of the hospital.

760
00:58:28,818 --> 00:58:30,319
Why would he need to take a cab to go out?

761
00:58:32,446 --> 00:58:34,949
Maybe he just went to find
a better chicken soup place or something.

762
00:58:36,242 --> 00:58:38,702
That's ridiculous. Hey!

763
00:58:40,538 --> 00:58:43,124
He took a taxi to escape
and then decided to come back.

764
00:58:43,207 --> 00:58:45,584
Then he just shows up out of nowhere
saying he wants to help us?

765
00:58:46,210 --> 00:58:48,838
He's definitely up to something.

766
00:58:49,255 --> 00:58:50,714
But he seemed pretty clueless.

767
00:58:50,840 --> 00:58:52,424
You really think he could plan all this?

768
00:58:52,508 --> 00:58:55,511
He's Bulgae, not Bong Jae-sun.

769
00:58:55,719 --> 00:58:58,222
The master of disguise, Bulgae,
who can even change his voice.

770
00:58:58,305 --> 00:59:01,350
He's the kind of guy who'll stop
at nothing to complete his mission.

771
00:59:01,433 --> 00:59:03,227
Did you forget ten years ago
when he showed up

772
00:59:03,310 --> 00:59:04,812
on that ferry dressed as a woman?

773
00:59:06,105 --> 00:59:08,440
Him, acting all innocent
like this right now...

774
00:59:08,524 --> 00:59:09,692
It's nothing for a guy like him.

775
00:59:09,775 --> 00:59:12,236
So don't you let your guard down either.

776
00:59:12,319 --> 00:59:13,946
Okay, then if you knew
all that about Bulgae

777
00:59:14,029 --> 00:59:15,823
why did you agree to take him in?

778
00:59:15,906 --> 00:59:18,993
Mi-kyung and your wife
are at that K-Pop place or something.

779
00:59:19,076 --> 00:59:21,704
What if he shows his true colors
and does something to them?

780
00:59:22,163 --> 00:59:24,582
It would be better to just
get rid of him right now.

781
00:59:24,665 --> 00:59:27,001
Didn't you see
Prosecutor Gang's reaction earlier?

782
00:59:27,084 --> 00:59:28,961
Besides, everyone else
is completely convinced

783
00:59:29,044 --> 00:59:31,422
he's the naive Bong Je-sun.

784
00:59:31,505 --> 00:59:33,257
And he's putting on such a convincing act

785
00:59:33,340 --> 00:59:35,676
so it's useless for me
to go around saying he's Bulgae.

786
00:59:35,759 --> 00:59:37,803
It's better if I keep him close
and watch him.

787
00:59:37,887 --> 00:59:39,847
That way, we can figure out
what he's after.

788
00:59:39,930 --> 00:59:42,516
And then we can use it against him.

789
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:45,269
So you keep your eyes peeled
and watch him closely.

790
00:59:46,729 --> 00:59:49,023
- He's coming.
- So he is, that jerk.

791
00:59:50,858 --> 00:59:53,027
Oh, sorry about that.
I got caught up talking.

792
00:59:53,110 --> 00:59:55,446
At least you know that. You drive.

793
00:59:59,158 --> 01:00:01,160
JEONGSEOK BOARDING HOUSE

794
01:00:03,829 --> 01:00:06,999
- Nam-il.
- Oh, Uncle!

795
01:00:07,082 --> 01:00:08,792
Are you okay, Uncle?

796
01:00:10,920 --> 01:00:12,171
What happened?

797
01:00:12,463 --> 01:00:13,839
Are you allowed to leave
the hospital already?

798
01:00:14,924 --> 01:00:18,427
- I'm much better now. I'm fine.
- I know, but still.

799
01:00:18,510 --> 01:00:20,387
It's not like you're the Hulk. Jeez.

800
01:00:25,517 --> 01:00:27,561
Who... who are they?

801
01:00:28,729 --> 01:00:30,356
They're just some people I know.

802
01:00:31,106 --> 01:00:33,651
- Why are you alone? Where's everyone?
- What?

803
01:00:34,276 --> 01:00:37,988
The lady from the Chinese restaurant
came by with her kid earlier.

804
01:00:39,990 --> 01:00:44,370
- Daddy!
- Oh, Ji-woo, you're here.

805
01:00:44,453 --> 01:00:45,996
You came?

806
01:00:49,792 --> 01:00:52,920
- Thank you.
- I still don't trust you 100%.

807
01:00:53,212 --> 01:00:55,756
I only came because of Ji-woo,
so don't get the wrong idea.

808
01:00:56,507 --> 01:00:57,800
I know.

809
01:00:57,883 --> 01:00:59,176
You did well.

810
01:01:00,177 --> 01:01:02,471
But where's your father?

811
01:01:03,180 --> 01:01:06,100
I don't know. He said he was going
to close up the shop and come

812
01:01:06,183 --> 01:01:08,102
but then he said
a large group of customers showed up

813
01:01:08,185 --> 01:01:09,186
so he isn't coming.

814
01:01:09,270 --> 01:01:11,355
Still, you should have
brought him with you.

815
01:01:11,480 --> 01:01:13,399
He said he wouldn't come.
What was I supposed to do?

816
01:01:13,941 --> 01:01:17,403
My dad's mad because of you,
so you go deal with him yourself.

817
01:01:17,486 --> 01:01:19,321
Jeez.

818
01:01:20,322 --> 01:01:22,574
All right. I'll go get him.

819
01:01:23,200 --> 01:01:25,244
- Ji-woo, stay here for a minute.
- Okay.

820
01:01:26,662 --> 01:01:29,581
You explain the situation to people
when they get here.

821
01:01:30,207 --> 01:01:31,250
And...

822
01:01:36,630 --> 01:01:39,717
- Keep a close eye on Bulgae.
- Yes, got it.

823
01:01:44,763 --> 01:01:46,849
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

824
01:01:59,528 --> 01:02:03,198
Prosecutor Gang? Long time no see.

825
01:02:03,282 --> 01:02:05,701
Are you back from your leave today?

826
01:02:06,785 --> 01:02:08,203
I'm sorry, Chief Prosecutor.

827
01:02:09,330 --> 01:02:10,873
I'm sorry I didn't answer your calls

828
01:02:11,248 --> 01:02:14,293
and missed my return date.
I truly have no excuse.

829
01:02:14,376 --> 01:02:17,504
Hey, that's not like you.
No need to apologize.

830
01:02:18,756 --> 01:02:20,758
Judging by how well you look

831
01:02:21,133 --> 01:02:23,218
you must have had a good time off.

832
01:02:23,302 --> 01:02:27,139
I am so sorry. I'll accept any punishment.

833
01:02:30,768 --> 01:02:32,061
You can go.

834
01:02:32,811 --> 01:02:35,481
- Sir?
- Isn't your return report finished?

835
01:02:35,981 --> 01:02:38,108
- I said, you can go.
- But Mr. Kim said

836
01:02:38,650 --> 01:02:40,444
that you were desperately looking for me.

837
01:02:40,527 --> 01:02:43,947
That was then, and this is now.

838
01:02:44,990 --> 01:02:46,950
Or what? You want to stay
and write a formal apology?

839
01:02:47,076 --> 01:02:49,286
No, sir. Really.

840
01:02:49,370 --> 01:02:52,706
I'm so sorry.
Thank you so much. Take care, sir.

841
01:03:06,637 --> 01:03:07,805
Yes.

842
01:03:08,097 --> 01:03:11,058
Just as you said,
Gang Yeong-ae came to work.

843
01:03:11,809 --> 01:03:13,685
I'll put my people on her.

844
01:03:14,144 --> 01:03:17,022
We won't lose her like last time.

845
01:03:24,029 --> 01:03:26,740
Hey, why are you here?
O-ran's already there.

846
01:03:26,824 --> 01:03:29,118
I told you yesterday.
It's dangerous right now.

847
01:03:29,201 --> 01:03:31,453
You need to close
the restaurant for a while.

848
01:03:32,162 --> 01:03:33,455
You said you understood yesterday.

849
01:03:33,539 --> 01:03:36,667
I said I'd convince O-ran.
When did I say I would leave?

850
01:03:36,750 --> 01:03:39,711
And who are you
to decide to close the business?

851
01:03:40,796 --> 01:03:43,715
Come on, you've been wanting a break.
Just think of this as a vacation.

852
01:03:43,841 --> 01:03:46,593
But how can I think of it as a vacation
when it's not?

853
01:03:46,718 --> 01:03:49,263
To you, this may just be a restaurant
you worked at reluctantly

854
01:03:49,346 --> 01:03:53,684
but O-ran's mother and I
poured our youth into building this place.

855
01:03:53,767 --> 01:03:57,729
Does it make any sense to close down
because of some thugs?

856
01:03:57,813 --> 01:04:01,066
- Father.
- You go and take care of O-ran.

857
01:04:01,608 --> 01:04:05,154
I can handle this restaurant
just fine on my own.

858
01:04:15,247 --> 01:04:18,250
Go on upstairs and get some rest.
I'll close up.

859
01:04:19,251 --> 01:04:21,503
I haven't been able to come
to the restaurant much lately.

860
01:04:22,671 --> 01:04:23,839
All right, then.

861
01:04:24,590 --> 01:04:26,425
Finish up and come upstairs.

862
01:04:43,525 --> 01:04:44,943
We're closed.

863
01:05:17,893 --> 01:05:19,728
Long time no see, Ho-myeong.

864
01:05:27,069 --> 01:05:29,613
SPECIAL THANKS
TO KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

865
01:05:44,378 --> 01:05:45,379
Do you and everyone around you

866
01:05:45,462 --> 01:05:47,381
have to be destroyed
before you learn your lesson?

867
01:05:47,464 --> 01:05:48,882
Is it okay for you to go up
against someone that dangerous?

868
01:05:48,966 --> 01:05:52,761
- Take care of that woman.
- I'll have to get some blood on my hands.

869
01:05:52,844 --> 01:05:54,471
That USB drive
with Han Gyeong-wook's weakness.

870
01:05:54,555 --> 01:05:56,723
It means that the package has surfaced.

871
01:05:56,807 --> 01:05:59,977
Those two have the missing package.

872
01:06:00,060 --> 01:06:02,229
We just have to make Bulgae talk
and get the package.

873
01:06:02,312 --> 01:06:03,855
Agent Bulgae of the Ministry
of People's Armed Forces.

874
01:06:03,981 --> 01:06:05,440
A human weapon trained in North Korea.

875
01:06:05,524 --> 01:06:07,025
-What?
-What?

876
01:06:07,109 --> 01:06:08,110
I think you've got it wrong.

877
01:06:08,193 --> 01:06:10,195
I'm telling you,
I really don't remember a thing.

878
01:06:10,279 --> 01:06:12,197
He says he can't remember anything.
How are you supposed to make him talk?

879
01:06:12,281 --> 01:06:13,282
Tie him up.

880
01:06:14,032 --> 01:06:15,784
- You've really gone too far.
- Stop.

881
01:06:15,909 --> 01:06:18,370
- Everyone will be in danger.
- We're not far from the finish line.

882
01:06:18,453 --> 01:06:19,454
We need to strike first.

883
01:06:19,538 --> 01:06:21,790
Hey, Bulgae. Now make your choice.

